<!--
Paste this block into your project's AGENTS.md or REASONIX.md (loaded into every
session). It makes the "check skills first" discipline always-on — the Reasonix
equivalent of the Claude Code SessionStart injection, since Reasonix hooks cannot
inject SessionStart output into context.
-->

## Skills

At the start of every task — before acting, exploring, or asking clarifying
questions — scan the pinned skills index and load the relevant skill with
`run_skill` (or `read_skill` in plan mode). If there's even a small chance a
skill applies, load it to check.

Start with the **using-superpowers** skill; it routes to the rest. Process
skills come first: **superpowers-brainstorming** before building, **superpowers-systematic-debugging**
before fixing, **superpowers-writing-plans** before multi-step work, and
**superpowers-verification-before-completion** before claiming anything is done.
